prohibit /prəˈhɪbɪt/

(prohibiting,prohibited,prohibits) 

1. V-T If a law or someone in authority prohibits something, they forbid it or make it illegal. 禁止 [正式] 

例： ...a law that prohibits tobacco advertising in newspapers and magazines. …一项禁止在报纸和杂志上刊登烟草广告的法律。 

例： Fishing is prohibited. 捕鱼是受禁止的。 

2. prohibition N-UNCOUNT 禁止 

例： The air force and the navy retain their prohibition of women on air combat missions. 空军和海军都保留了对女性空中作战任务的禁止。

</div>

